title: Study of isomer ratios of proton-nuclear cross sections on tin isotopes.

x4freetext: Study of isomer ratios of proton-nuclear cross sections
on tin isotopes.
.Armenian state university.

x4codes.hlp: Joint Institute for Nuclear Research (JINR), Dubna
Nuclear Physics Institute of Czech Acad. Sci., Rez, Czech Republic

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physics of Atomic Nuclei, Vol.59, p.560 (1996)

x4freetext: English translation
English translation of `YF` was added
Targets Sn-112,Sn-118 and Sn-124 were used.Enrichment-
Three layer foils from Sn-118 and Sn-124,with dimension
2*2 cm,were set under beam.Thickness one layer was
67 and 74 mg/cm**2,accordingly. Sn-112 target has
thickness 390 mg/cm**2.

x4codes.hlp: Joint Institute for Nuclear Research (JINR), Dubna

x4freetext: Dependences of the isomer ratios of the cross sections
and of the behavior of the high-spin and low-spin
states on the number of emitted protons are obtained
for several residual nuclei.
measurement of gamma-activity were started after 1 and
1.5 Hour for Sn-124,Sn-118 targets and after 4 hour for
Sn-112  targets  and  were repeatedly measured over a
period of one year.
.All uncertainties are statistical.
.Table 1 and 2 of J,YF,59,592,1996
Some decay data were used by authors are incorrect.
